      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a pretty strong take. so u think the whole system is basically broken? i see people arguing that the UN is actually kind of essential because without it things like the Ukraine situation would've been even worse. is that view considered a mainstream historical perspective too, or is the \"failure\" argument more dominant?",
